===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|え}}

{{IPAchar|/je/}} → {{IPAchar|/e/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=え|-}}. The ''ye'' pronunciation merged with ''e'' in {{w|Early Middle Japanese}}. The merged sound was ''ye'' until the {{w|Edo period}}, which is found in ''[[Yedo]]'', ''[[yen]]'' and ''{{w|Yebisu}}''.

This term was so representative of the ''ye'' reading that it lent its shape to the {{w|hentaigana}} {{m|ja|𛀁|tr=ye}}.

